Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Heat a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic and
cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Add @water{3/4%cup}
and bring to a boil. Once boiling, stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Reduce heat,
cover, and cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered until ready to
serve.

Zest @lemon{2} until you have 1 tsp; quarter lemons. Quarter 1
@Persian cucumber{2} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick triangles.
Dice 1 @Roma tomato{2}. (Save remaining cucumber and tomato for lunch.) Halve
and peel @shallot{1}. Thinly slice one half; mince other half until you have 2
TBSP. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems. Mince stems; save leaves for
garnish.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine diced tomato, sliced cucumber, minced shallot,
parsley stems, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. In a #small bowl{}, combine 4 TBSP
@?sour cream{6%tbsp}, lemon zest, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. In another small bowl, combine sliced shallot with
@red wine vinegar{5%tsp} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{20%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Mediterranean spice blend{1%tbsp}. Heat a large
drizzle of olive oil in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan
and let rest.

Pour out any excess oil from pan, then add @butter{2%tbsp} and juice from 1
lemon wedge and heat over medium-high heat. Stir to combine and melt butter.
Fluff rice with a #fork and divide between plates. Arrange half the chicken on
top. Pour butter sauce over chicken, then dollop with crema. Arrange
cucumber salad to the side and sprinkle with half the @feta cheese{1%cup},
half the pickled shallot, and all of the parsley leaves. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.

== Lunch Wrap ==

When you're ready to prep lunch, cut remaining chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Halve remaining cucumber lengthwise, then cut lengthwise into thin sticks. Slice
remaining tomato into thin rounds. Spread @flour tortilla{2} with remaining
sour cream, then fill each with remaining feta, remaining pickled shallot,
chicken, cucumber, and tomato. Roll into wraps and pack in #reusable containers{}.
Keep refrigerated before enjoying (we recommend eating chilled or at room
temperature).

> The nutrition facts panel represents the nutrient values for the
> Mediterranean Chicken Dinner. The Lunch Wrap information is as follows:
> Calories: 490, Fat: 19 g, Saturated Fat: 10 g, Carbohydrate: 40 g, Sugar: 4 g,
> Fiber: 1 g, Protein: 35 g, Cholesterol: 140 mg, Sodium: 850 mg.